The size of the public debt of Italy increased to record levels
The size of Italy’s public debt in June 2016 exceeded 2.248 trillion euros.
The Central Bank of the country said that this amount is a historical maximum, reports RIA Novosti.
The previous record was set in May this year.
Then the size of the national debt reached 2.228 trillion euros.
It is noted that in the first half of the year, the debt load of Italy increased by 77.2 billion euros.
Earlier it was reported that at the end of 2015, Italy’s public debt amounted to 132.7% of the country’s GDP.
Meanwhile, Italian Minister of Economy and Finance Pier Carlo Padoan predicted a decrease in this indicator in 2016 to 130.9%, and in 2018 to 123.4% of GDP.
Payments from the airport received 141 victims of the terrorist attack in Domodedovo.
141 people received charitable payments from the Fund "Aviation", which was created by the management of the airport "Domodedovo" to help victims of the terrorist attack in 2011, Interfax reports.
According to airport spokesman Alexander Vlasov, two more statements are currently under consideration.
“The foundation continues to provide charitable payments to victims of the terrorist attack of 2011 and provides comprehensive assistance in resolving existing issues,” Vlasov added, recalling that a website of the foundation was created specifically to facilitate interaction with the victims, containing complete information about the procedure for providing charitable assistance.
In 2011, a suicide bomber detonated an explosive device in the arrival hall of foreign airlines Domodedovo.
As a result of the attack, 37 people were killed, 172 more were injured.
Scientists have found an animal that can live for 500 years
An international team of biologists has concluded that the longest-lived vertebrate is the Greenland polar shark, which can live for about 500 years, reports RT.
Scientists conducted a radiocarbon analysis of the lens of the eye of 28 Greenland sharks.
The largest shark, whose length exceeds five meters, can be from 272 to 512 years.
Biologists believe that a low metabolism plays an important role in the longevity of the shark, which leads to slow development.
Female Greenland sharks only reach sexual maturity by 150 years of age.
Previously it was believed that the longest living all vertebrates "neighbor" sharks - the Greenland whale.
The oldest known individual was just over 210 years old.
