The company does not know who is playing Pokémon Go, it just sees the primary data on the passage of levels.
Many health campaigns urging people to "find 30 minutes", "get off the couch" and "be active every day" have found no response because most health messages are boring and are spoken by people who look miserable.
However, the importance of exercise should not be underestimated.
Those who exercise regularly have a lower chance of developing cancer or depression.
Physical activity helps with weight correction, high blood pressure, diabetes and another long list of benefits, too long to cite here.
But the beauty of Pokémon Go is that it pulls people outside to do what they love.
Thus, three fundamentals of health are covered: movement, fresh air and sunlight and joy.
Some people even make new friends on the hunt.
As usual, there are boring people who are looking for something to complain about.
And yes, someone might come across the door.
So what?
The breakthrough happened.
After all, despite the fact that applications for smartphones, such as Fitbit could previously track our physical activity, they did not give us a reason to practice, as this game gives.
The novelty will ache, and the use will weaken with time.
However, because of the success of Pokemon, there will be more games that will combine apps and virtual reality with physical activity in the real world, helping many people hunt to be more active, fit and healthy.
