According to him, the possible resumption of charters is good news, but it will not affect the balance of power in the market too much, because the main buyers of charter tours - families with children - have already returned from vacation and are preparing for school or are on vacation in other countries.
During the velvet season, tours are bought mainly by solo travelers and couples.
Charter programs can count on those who have the opportunity to relax spontaneously,” says Pavel Rumyantsev.
“Turkey has a chance to attract a lot of tourists if it now gives a very budget proposals - 50-60 thousand rubles for a tour for two, because there are people who are deliberately waiting for very cheap tours,” says Valeria Rosenthal, CEO of the travel agency Optio-Travel.
