The WTO panel of arbitrators found that Russian import duties on paper, refrigerators and palm oil are contrary to the rules of the organization.
Import rates exceed the obligations assumed by Russia upon accession to the WTO.
"This is the first time that the WTO has taken a decision against Russia," the WTO said in a statement on its website.
However, the arbitrators stressed in their opinion that the European Union did not provide sufficient evidence that Russia’s measures were “systematic” or “comprehensive”.
Russia, in turn, promised in the near future to adapt import duties on paper and refrigerators.
This is stated in the message of the Ministry of economic development of Russia.
On July 4, it was reported that Kiev intends to complain to the World Trade Organization about the actions of Russia, which imposed additional restrictions on the transit of Ukrainian goods.
This is stated in the statement of the government of Ukraine.
In May, the Financial Times wrote that the US behavior in resolving controversial issues in the WTO undermines the principles of discussion adopted by the organization.
Such a statement was made by Brazil, Japan, the European Union and other WTO members due to the refusal of the Americans to approve for a second term South Korean judge Jang Song Hwa.
In this regard, Russia will not apply to the WTO on the issue of Western sanctions imposed against Russia.
The WTO is an international organization established in January 1995 to liberalize international trade.
It now consists of 162 countries.
Russia joined in 2012.
