The Russian Copper Company (RMK) is ready to take on social responsibility and pay more attention to the environmental aspects of its business.
This is confirmed, for example, by the fact that RMK took up the modernization of one of the oldest and environmentally "dirty" enterprises in the country - the Karabash copper smelting plant.
Karabash copper smelting plant was founded by an English joint stock company headed by Leslie Urquhart in 1910.
In Soviet times, it was a significant industrial enterprise for the country's economy, and it actually ensured the life of the whole city.
However, in the 1990s, due to financial problems, production was stopped, which led to serious social problems in Karabash.
In 1998, it was decided to resume the work of the Karabash copper smelting plant.
It was also necessary to solve one of the main problems of the Karabash plant - environmental.
By the early 2000s, Karabash was already notorious as an environmental disaster zone.
The situation at Karabashmedy began to change in 2004, after the company came under the control of the Russian Copper Company.
The company began to modernize production, which began to gradually reduce the environmental burden on the environment.
This was recently noted by the Governor of the Chelyabinsk region Boris Dubrovsky, who visited Karabashmed in early July.
The head of the South Urals called grandiose changes that have occurred with the enterprise since Karabashmed moved to the RMK group.
The main event for the modernization of Karabashmedy in recent years was the construction of a new sulfuric acid workshop, which allows to capture up to 99.9% of metallurgical gases.
According to the president of the Russian Copper Company Vsevolod Levin, the volume of investments in this project amounted to about 7 billion rubles.
The next stage of modernization of Karabashmed CJSC is the reconstruction of the converter repartition.
Replacement of three converters, sprayers, gas pipeline is planned for the end of 2017.
The cost of the project is 2.5 billion rubles.
In addition, at the end of 2016, it is planned to launch a new workshop for cleaning industrial wastewater worth 1 billion rubles.
In turn, the amount of taxes deducted to the budget of the city of Karabash will increase.
For the entire period of implementation of the Tominsky GOK project - from the beginning of construction to the commissioning of the second stage - the federal treasury will receive 8.9 billion rubles.
And after the commissioning of the GOK, the receipt of taxes in budgets of all levels can amount to 80.9 billion rubles.
For the year of production in the Varna region, 346.3 million rubles were transferred to budgets of different levels.
And that's for the first year.
“The longer the enterprise is successfully operating, the amount of deductions can be higher,” Valery Ulanovsky added.
In RMK said that in 2015 the tax deductions from Mikheevsky GOK approached 1 billion rubles.
However, the participation of RMK enterprises in the life and development of the territories of their presence is not limited to tax deductions.
RMK enterprises help repair and maintain schools, kindergartens, sports facilities, build cultural and entertainment facilities, and improve territories.
