In particular, Russian exports to Iran grew by 91.5 percent and amounted to 697 million dollars.
Russian imports from Iran increased by 16 percent, to $158 million.
The increase in trade was achieved thanks to the supply of machinery, ground vehicles and weapons," the ambassador said.
Dzhagaryan also predicts that a record number of Iranian tourists will visit Russia this year.
