In an apparent attempt to kill himself, the victim, a Swiss woman aged 49, was hit by several vehicles, including a truck.
She died on the spot.
Several drivers involved have already been interviewed, but the identity of some has not yet been established, police said, calling on them and anyone else who witnessed the incident to respond.
A criminal case was opened, a "logical" step in such a situation, lawyer Gilles Hofstetter Le Tribune de Geneve said.
However, it remains to be seen whether any of the drivers involved will be charged.
Was it possible to avoid a hit?
That’s what the prosecutor should determine,” Hofstetter said.
Two other similar cases over the past five years suggest that drivers will not be held responsible.
In each case — both of which involve a person walking in the dark on the freeway — it was ruled that motorists could not expect a chance encounter with a pedestrian on the freeway in the middle of the night.
Last year, the officer was acquitted of causing death by negligence after she struck and killed a man lying on an A1 near Pyern on the night of August 2014.
22-year-old victim drank and lost consciousness on the road, heard the court.
