Notifications for transport tax will cease to be sent by mail - website Driving www.zr.ru
The Tax Inspectorate changed the procedure for sending notifications about property taxes.
All Russian car owners are accustomed to the scheme that has not changed over the years: in summer and autumn they receive by mail receipts for payment of transport tax for the previous year.
However, this year many of them will not wait.
The fact is that the tax inspectorate has quietly changed the procedure for notifying citizens.
For those who are registered in the "Personal Account of the taxpayer" on the official website of the department nalog.ru, notifications will come in electronic form.
The inspection automatically considered such Russians to be online users and deleted them from the standard, “paper” mailing list.
The novelty will affect all owners of vehicles and real estate.
Everyone else will continue to receive the usual letters.
However, there is an opportunity to return to the old scheme and the owners of the account on the site.
To do this, they will have to visit the tax office during August and write a statement.
On the one hand, the new order is more modern and more convenient.
The notification will appear in the "personal cabinet" immediately after drafting, while the letter will go for several days and may be completely lost.
In addition, the number of users of the Internet service of the tax inspectorate exceeded 18 million people, which will allow the department to seriously save on mailing.
On the other hand, the modest news on the inspection website is clearly not enough to inform citizens about the changed order.
Some could register in the "personal cabinet" for a one-time service and have long forgotten about it.
These people will not wait for notification by mail and, without knowing it, will fall into the category of non-payers with all the ensuing consequences.
Access to the "Personal Account of the taxpayer" is carried out in three ways: through the account of the portal gosuslugi.ru, using an electronic signature or entering the login and password specified in the registration card.
The latter can be obtained personally at any tax office (regardless of the place of registration).
