Tuning Mercedes-Benz G-class, in which improvements are aimed at achieving very high returns, is a thing in itself.
But the controversial concept did not confuse the masters of the company G-Power, who took up the modification of the sports version of the Mercedes-AMG G 63.
G-Power is known for its passion for BMW cars, but nothing human is alien to its masters.
Indeed, why not improve the G 63 - 571-strong flying sledgehammer with aerodynamics of the tank and acceleration to hundreds in 5.4 seconds?
Inflating the "muscles" of the crazy "helik", the masters took advantage of the 5.5-liter supercharged "eight".
But the dynamics of acceleration to a hundred has improved by an indistinguishable 0.1 s, and now the flying “brick” is capable of a breakthrough in 5.3 s.
However, accelerations from medium speeds probably give it much better.
The speed ceiling is frightening: if the standard G 63 does not drive faster than 210 km / h, then the tuning all-terrain vehicle with a deactivated electronic “collar” is able to squeeze 250 km / h.
Outside, the car is almost indistinguishable from its factory source, with the exception of other wheels - 23-inch Hurricane RR with a dimension of 305/35 ZR 23.
